Noto Sans Ethiopic Thin Regular (NotoSansEthiopic-Thin.ttf)

STAT

static font

Variable font must have a STAT table.

No check of STAT table for static fonts included, yet. Static fonts do not need to have a STAT table. It is only recommended by Microsoft, not required.
More infos here:
https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/typography/opentype/spec/stat

More infos here:
https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/typography/opentype/spec/stat

Noto Sans Ethiopic Thin Regular (NotoSansEthiopic-Thin.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Noto Sans Ethiopic' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'Noto Sans Ethiopic Thin'.

Pass

Noto Sans Ethiopic ExtLt Regular (NotoSansEthiopic-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Sans Ethiopic ExtraLight' ≠ 'Noto Sans Ethiopic ExtLt' (NID 1).

Noto Sans Ethiopic Light Regular (NotoSansEthiopic-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSansEthiopic-Light', Everything looks good.

Noto Sans Ethiopic Light Regular (NotoSansEthiopic-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Noto Sans Ethiopic' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Noto Sans Ethiopic Light'.

Noto Sans Ethiopic Med Regular (NotoSansEthiopic-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSansEthiopic-Medium', Everything looks good.

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Sans Ethiopic Medium' ≠ 'Noto Sans Ethiopic Med' (NID 1).

Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSansEthiopic-SemiBold', Everything looks good.

Pass

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Sans Ethiopic SemiBold' ≠ 'Noto Sans Ethiopic SemBd' (NID 1).
